.TH "lpfc_issue_fabric_reglogin" 9 "lpfc_issue_fabric_reglogin" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
lpfc_issue_fabric_reglogin \- Issue fabric registration login for a vport
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" lpfc_issue_fabric_reglogin
.BI "(struct lpfc_vport *vport "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "vport" 12
pointer to a host virtual N_Port data structure.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This routine issues a fabric registration login for a \fIvport\fP. An
active ndlp node with Fabric_DID must already exist for this \fIvport\fP.
The routine invokes two mailbox commands to carry out fabric registration
login through the HBA firmware: the first mailbox command requests the
HBA to perform link configuration for the \fIvport\fP; and the second mailbox
command requests the HBA to perform the actual fabric registration login
with the \fIvport\fP.

Return code
0 - successfully issued fabric registration login for \fIvport\fP
-ENXIO -- failed to issue fabric registration login for \fIvport\fP
